title: MS-12633 spec is worth using in a Hemi
description: The "0" part of 0w-40 gives it a low enough viscosity to get oil up to the cam and roller-lifter assembly, which is prone to under-lubrication in current-generation (apx '09-present) Hemis, and especially in ones that idle a lot.  MS-12633 is a "Taxi-Specification": meaning for vehicles that idle a lot.  Hemi's a great engine but it's picky about the oil it needs.  This is the right stuff at a good price.
date: Reviewed in the United States on March 14, 2023

title: What a deal!  Cheapest I can find it
description: I've running this in my hemi ram for 4 oil changes now. Ram says 5w20 but thats just the epa sticking their noses where they dont belong.  I do oil changes roughly every 4k. Also running a bottle of liqui-moly. Oil pressure never drops below 46psi and valvetrain is the quietest it's ever been. I have MDS disabled and no engine light.
date: Reviewed in the United States on March 13, 2023

title: Just want I needed for a great price

title: Just what my SRT392 needs!! Priced...okay.
description: This is the factory recommended oil for my SRT392, and all 6.4L Hemi engines.  Price is high compared to any other penzoil oil, but its most likely a less used oil viscosity.  Don't get the purple stuff or the amsoil stuff.... you'll regret it if you drive your beast hard.
